<recipe xmlns="https://cazzscookingcommunity.github.io"
        xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
        xsi:schemaLocation="https://cazzscookingcommunity.github.io ../../xml/recipe.xsd">
  <title>Jasmine's Red Lentil Dhal</title>
  <filename>jasmines_red_lentil_dhal.xml</filename>
  <thumbnail>jasmines_red_lentil_dhal.jpeg</thumbnail>
  <category>Dinner</category>
  <diet>Vegetarian</diet>
  <yield>4</yield>
  <prepTime>P15</prepTime>
  <cookTime>P45</cookTime>
  <part>
    <title>Main</title>
    <ingredient>1 cup red lentils</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1.5 lt stock</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1 tsp turmeric</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1 tsp salt</ingredient>
    <ingredient>2 handfuls spinach</ingredient>
    <ingredient>4 cups water</ingredient>
    <step>Roughly chop spinach.</step>
    <step>Add the first 5 ingredients to a pot. Bring to a boil, then turn down to a simmer.</step>
    <step>Simmer for 45 minutes or until lentils loose their shape.</step>
  </part>
  <part>
    <title>Curry Blend</title>
    <ingredient>50 gms unsalted butter</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1 tsp cumin seeds</ingredient>
    <ingredient>4 cloves of garlic</ingredient>
    <ingredient>3 whole dried chillies or 1 tsp chilli flakes</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1/2 tsp garam masala</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1/2 tsp paprika</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1/2 tsp salt</ingredient>
    <step>While lentils are cooking. Melt butter in a fry pan and add salt and cumin seeds</step>
    <step>Once cummin seeds begin to sputter, add garlic and other spices.</step>
    <step>Cook for a further minute and remove from heat.</step>
    <step>Once the lentils are done and the curry blend is ready, pour the curry blend over the lentils and serve with rice and Greek Yogurt.</step>
  </part>
  <htmlFilename>jasmines_red_lentil_dhal.html</htmlFilename>
</recipe>
